    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>black</strong> <strong>olives</strong> roughly</p><p>Chop your <strong>capers</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-plant-based-tortiglioni-puttanesca/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-plant-based-tortiglioni-puttanesca/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 375ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[500ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-plant-based-tortiglioni-puttanesca/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and <strong>dried basil </strong>to the pot with your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped olives </strong>and <strong>capers</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-plant-based-tortiglioni-puttanesca/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pot with your <strong>tortiglioni </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 12-15 min, stirring occasionally, until the pasta is cooked through and the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-plant-based-tortiglioni-puttanesca/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the tortiglioni is cooking, chop your <strong>parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-plant-based-tortiglioni-puttanesca/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tortiglioni is cooked, stir through the <strong>spinach </strong>with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a splash of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 1 min or until the spinach has wilted \u2013\u00a0this is your <strong>one pot plant-based tortiglioni puttanesca</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-plant-based-tortiglioni-puttanesca/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot plant-based tortiglioni puttanesca </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and garnish with the <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
